fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
A twisting function \tau is a family of maps \tau_n : B_n \to G_{n-1} such that
\begin{aligned}     \tau(\partial_k b) &= \partial_k \tau(b) && (k < n-1)\\     \tau(\partial_{n-1} b) &= \partial_{n-1} \tau(b) \cdot \tau(\partial_n b) \\     \tau(\sigma_k b) &= \sigma_k \tau(b) && (k < n)\\     \tau(\sigma_n b) &= 1   \end{aligned}
The corresponding simplicial map B_n \to ({\bar{W}} G)_n is then computed by discarding the last k vertices of the input b \in B_n for 1 \le k \le n, apply them to \tau and placing them at the correct components.
